@shekharshank great, it sounds like you discovered the solution to the tiny mAP bug another user found!

In relation to the training, it sounds like everything is fine. Full training takes 273 epochs, so you are  about 30% done. You can plot your training results with `from utils import utils; utils.plot_results()`.

If you are looking for higher mAP, I recommend you move to YOLOv3-SPP, which is the default network for training. If you have substantial computational resources you can also run hyperparameter evolution using `python3 train.py -evolve`.

@glenn-jocher I was using the size 416 without the flag --multi-scale
And the results file is attached..but its only from epoch 121...I lost the results from the first 120 epochs, but the graph in the previous comment shows the numbers... I will train again with the correct mask in the cfg and with pretrained yolov3-tiny.weights
[results.txt](https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/files/3501711/results.txt)
